cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about using deep convolutional neural networks for automatic brain tumor segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and uncertainty estimation, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper being related to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
